This paper presents a flapping-wing robot that uses its wings for environmental perception and navigation in tight spaces without the need for visual feedback. The paper focuses on the design and implementation of the robot, as well as the interpretation of wing loading feedback to detect environmental changes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.ROB (Robotics and Automation), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
